Package: staggeredGMM
Title: GMM Estimation of Treatment Effects under Staggered Adoption
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rishabh", "Bijani", , "rishabhbijani@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Parush", "Arora", , "parush.arora@ashoka.edu.in", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Implements the generalized method of moments (GMM) estimator
    for cohort-and-time-specific average treatment effects (CATTs) under
    staggered treatment adoption developed in Arora and Bijani, "Estimating
    Treatment Effects under Staggered Timing and Non-Spherical Errors".
    Clean (never-treated or not-yet-treated) two-by-two difference-in-
    differences comparisons are stacked as GMM moment conditions, reduced to
    a design-sized minimal basis via a reduced-space singular value
    decomposition, and weighted by the inverse of an estimated moment
    covariance under a pooled Toeplitz, cohort-specific Toeplitz, or fully
    unrestricted within-cohort covariance model. Optional baseline-covariate
    adjustment via outcome regression is supported for all three estimators.
